TRANSLATION
He who knows Me as the unborn, as the beginningless, as the Supreme Lord of all the worlds\xc3\x91he, undeluded among men, is freed from all sins.'

PURPORTAs stated in the Seventh Chapter, those who are trying to elevate themselves to the platform of spiritual realization are not ordinary men. They are superior to millions and millions of ordinary men who have no knowledge of spiritual realization, but out of those actually trying to understand their spiritual situation, one who can come to the understanding that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead, the proprietor of everything, the unborn, is the most successful spiritually realized person. In that stage only, when one has fully understood K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa\xc3\x95s supreme position, can one be free completely from all sinful reactions.Here the word ajam, meaning unborn, should not be confused with the living entities, who are described in the Second Chapter as ajam. The Lord is different from the living entities who are taking birth and dying due to \nmaterial attachment. The conditional souls are changing their bodies, but His body is not changeable. Even when He comes to this material world, He comes as the same unborn; therefore in the Fourth Chapter it is said that the Lord, by His internal potency, is not under the inferior material energy, but is always in the superior energy.He was existing before the creation, and He is different from His creation. All the demigods were created within this material world, but as far as K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is \nconcerned, it is said that He is not created; therefore K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is different even from the great demigods like Brahm\xe2\x88\x92 and \xe2\x80\xa1iva. And because He is the creator of Brahm\xe2\x88\x92, \xe2\x80\xa1iva and all the other demigods, He is the Supreme Person of all planets.\xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9d K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is therefore different from everything that is created, and anyone who knows Him as such immediately becomes liberated from all sinful reaction. One must be liberated from all sinful activities to be in the \nknowledge of the Supreme Lord. Only by devotional service can He be known and not by any other means, as stated in Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92.One should not try to understand K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as a human being. As stated previously, only a foolish person thinks Him to be a human being. This is again expressed here in a different way. A man who is not foolish, who is intelligent enough to understand the constitutional position of the Godhead, is always free from all sinful reactions.'
If K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is known as the son of Devak\xe2\x80\x9d, then how can He be unborn? That is also explained in \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam: When He appeared before Devak\xe2\x80\x9d and Vasudeva, He was not born as an ordinary child; He appeared in His original form, and then He transformed Himself into an ordinary child.Anything done under the direction of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is transcendental. It cannot be contaminated by the material reactions, which may be auspicious or inauspicious. The conception that there are things auspicious and inauspicious in the material world is more or less a mental concoction because there is \nnothing auspicious in the material world. Everything is inauspicious because the very material mask is inauspicious. We simply imagine it to be auspicious. Real auspiciousness depends on activities in K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa consciousness in full devotion and service. Therefore if we at all want our activities to he auspicious, then we should work under the directions of the Supreme Lord. Such directions are given in authoritative scriptures such as \xe2\x80\xa1r\xe2\x80\x9dmad-Bh\xe2\x88\x92gavatam and Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, or from a bona fide spiritual master. Because the spiritual master is the representative of the Supreme Lord, his direction is directly the direction of the Supreme Lord. The spiritual master, saintly persons and scriptures direct in the same way. There is no contradiction in these three sources. All actions done under such direction are free from the reactions of pious or impious activities of this material world. The transcendental attitude of the devotee in the performance of activities is actually that of renunciation, and this is called sanny\xe2\x88\x92sa. Anyone acting under \nthe direction of the Supreme Lord is actually a sanny\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x80\x9d and a yog\xe2\x80\x9d, and not the man who has simply taken the dress of the sanny\xe2\x88\x92s\xe2\x80\x9d, or a pseudo-yog\xe2\x80\x9d.
