Arjuna said: You are the Supreme Brahman, the ultimate, the supreme abode and purifier, the Absolute Truth and the eternal divine person. You are the primal God, transcendental and original, and You are the unborn and all-\npervading beauty. All the great sages such as N\xe2\x88\x92rada, Asita, Devala, and Vy\xe2\x88\x92sa \nproclaim this of You, and now You Yourself are declaring it to me.
PURPORTIn these two verses the Supreme Lord gives a chance to the modern philosopher, for here it is clear that the Supreme is different from the individual soul. Arjuna, after hearing the essential four verses of Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92 in this chapter, became completely free from all doubts and accepted K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as \nthe Supreme Personality of Godhead. He at once boldly declares, \xc3\x92You are Parambrahma, the Supreme Personality of Godhead.\xc3\x93 And previously K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa states that He is the originator of everything and everyone. Every demigod and \nevery human being is dependant on Him. Men and demigods, out of ignorance, think that they are absolute and independant of the Supreme Lord K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. That ignorance is removed perfectly by the discharge of devotional service. This is already explained in the previous verse by the Lord. Now by His grace, Arjuna is accepting Him as the Supreme Truth, in concordance with the Vedic injunction. It is not because K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is an intimate friend of Arjuna that he is flattering Him by calling Him the Supreme Personality of Godhead, the \nAbsolute Truth. Whatever Arjuna says in these two verses is confirmed by Vedic truth. Vedic injunctions affirm that only one who takes to devotional service to the Supreme Lord can understand Him, whereas others cannot. Each and every word of this verse spoken by Arjuna is confirmed by Vedic injunction.In the Kena Upani\xc5\x92ad it is stated that the Supreme Brahman is the rest for everything, and K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa has already explained that everything is resting on Him. \nThe Mu\xe2\x80\x9a\xc5\xb8aka Upani\xc5\x92ad confirms that the Supreme Lord, in whom everything is resting, can be realized only by those who engage constantly in thinking of Him. This constant thinking of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is smara\xe2\x80\x9aam, one of the methods of devotional service. It is only by devotional service to K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa that one can understand his position and get rid of this material body.'
In the Vedas the Supreme Lord is accepted as the purest of the pure. One who understands that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the purest of the pure can become purified from all sinful activities. One cannot be disinfected from sinful activities unless he surrenders unto the Supreme Lord. Arjuna\xc3\x95s acceptance of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa as the supreme pure complies with the injunctions of Vedic literature. This is also confirmed by great personalities, of whom N\xe2\x88\x92rada is the chief.K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is the Supreme Personality of Godhead, and one should always meditate upon Him and enjoy one\xc3\x95s transcendental relationship with Him. He is the \nsupreme existence. He is free from bodily needs, birth and death. Not only does Arjuna confirm this, but all the Vedic literatures. the Pur\xe2\x88\x92\xe2\x80\x9aas and histories. In all Vedic literatures K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is thus described, and the Supreme \nLord Himself also says in the Fourth Chapter, \xc3\x92Although I am unborn, I appear on this earth to establish religious principles.\xc3\x93 He is the supreme origin; He has no cause, for He is the cause of all causes, and everything is emanating from Him. This perfect knowledge can be had by the grace of the Supreme \nLord.Here Arjuna expresses himself through the grace of K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa. If we want to understand Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92, we should accept the statements in these two verses. This is called the parampar\xe2\x88\x92 system, acceptance of the disciplic succession. Unless one is in the disciplic succession, he cannot understand Bhagavad-g\xe2\x80\x9dt\xe2\x88\x92. It is not possible by so-called academic education. Unfortunately those proud of their academic education, despite so much \nevidence in Vedic literatures, stick to their obstinate conviction that K\xe2\x80\x9e\xc5\x92\xe2\x80\x9aa is an ordinary person.
